article.headline: Drake 73, Western Illinois 64
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Josh Robinson scored 21 points as Drake beat Western Illinois 73-64 Tuesday night. Drake (2-2) led 25-23 at the half and pulled away converting 17-of-29 from the field and 14-of-16 from the foul line. Drake got help from Lonnie Randolph with 17 points and eight rebounds and Nick Grant added 10. Drake's inside game proved to be the difference as they outscored Western Illinois 36-22 in the paint. The Bulldogs had 17 points off of offensive rebounds and converted 19-of-24 from the foul line while Western was 9-of-12. Western Illinois (0-6) was led by Doyle Cole with 17 points and Bobby Carter with 13. The Leathernecks got their fast break going outscoring Drake 16-6, but it wasn't enough.

venue.fullName: LeRoy A. Ufkes Court at Western Hall
